column3: fast growing population and slow growth of economy of which Human

column2: Pakistan faces numerous economic social & security challenges since
2007. These factors are matter of acute concern for the law enforcement
agencies as they provide the ideal environment for transnational organized
crime networks to flourish and exploit weaknesses in the system. In response

column3: the government of Pakistan has taken important

column2: steps in developing strategies to combat this crime and protect the rights of

column4: Prevention of Smuggling of Migrants Act 2018

column2: & Prevention of Trafficking in Person Act 2018 were enacted. This was
followed by establishment of Anti- Human Trafficking Circles under the
Jurisdiction of Federal Investigation Agency (FIA) to take legal action against
this menace. FIA also established Internal Accountability Unit to keep an eye
over its employees to ensure principle of zero tolerance against connivance of

column3: the Inter Agencies Task Force (IATF) comprising more than 15

column2: agencies were also established to check the porous border of Western
Pakistan. The Interpol and concerned Foreign Missions in Pakistan have also
been taken on board for arrest/ apprehension and deportation/ repatriation of
MWS/T wanted by FIA in these foreign countries.
